## 9. Summary

| | Logistic Regression | XGBoost |
|--|--|--|
| ROC-AUC | ~0.83 | ~0.89 |
| Interpretability | ✅ High | ⚠️ Medium |
| Handles class imbalance | ✅ | ✅ |
| Suitable for CRM scoring | ✅ | ✅ |

**XGBoost** is the recommended production model for monthly scoring runs.
**Logistic Regression** is retained as the explainability model — useful when a member disputes their risk classification (GDPR Art. 22).

### Key Takeaways
- The first 3 months of membership are the highest churn risk window → invest in onboarding
- Satisfaction score is the strongest single predictor → post-purchase surveys are worth the effort
- Privacy-safe features alone are sufficient for a high-accuracy model (~0.89 AUC) → data minimisation does not compromise analytics quality
